\description{
Ridge (joy) plot for visualising the distribution of a numeric variable across
multiple groups. Each group is rendered as a partially overlapping density
curve along the y-axis, making it easy to compare distribution shapes, central
tendency, and spread across categories.

The function supports both \strong{long} and \strong{wide} data formats:
\itemize{
\item \strong{Long form} (\code{in_form = "long"}, default) — a numeric column (\code{x}) plus a
factor column (\code{group_by}) whose levels become the y-axis ridges.
\item \strong{Wide form} (\code{in_form = "wide"}) — multiple numeric columns listed in
\code{group_by} are gathered internally into long form.
